It was a great first day of school at Selmaville. One of the best starts in years. Our new normal is very different but the Rockets have accepted this challenge.

Classes took advantage of being outside in the nice weather to socially distance and get a break from wearing their masks.

It was great to see all of the students again. Thanks to the parents for preparing your child for what is our new normal. Thanks also to the staff for their hours of preparation leading up to this day. What a team effort this day was!

It is a good day to be a Rocket! ðŸš€

The first day of school for Selmaville students will be Wednesday, August 19th. School will dismiss at 11:30 am that day.

Also, parents may drop off school supplies from 8 am until 5 pm on Monday and Tuesday this week in the main office. This is to lighten the load on the first day of school for our younger students especially. Students are welcome to bring their supplies on the first day of school.

As a reminder, you must wear a mask when you enter the school.

post_text:
Selmaville School is planning a reverse teacher appreciation day on Tuesday, May 5th from 5 to 6 PM as May 5th is officially teacher appreciation day. This will give the Selmaville staff an opportunity to recognize and thank the parents for their cooperation and teaching efforts over the past couple of months while the students have been away from school. There will be a thank you gift for each family that attends who has a child in kindergarten through 8th grade.

This will also be a Rocket Roundup event where all of the personal belongings will be returned to the students from this past year.

The final activity will be a chance for everyone who attends the event to congratulate Mrs. Shuler and Mrs. Bushue on their retirements.

We ask that everyone drive through the outer lane in front of the school and you must remain in your vehicles as you drive through. We hope to see all of our Selmaville families there. If it rains we will postpone the event to another evening.

post_text:
Reverse Teacher Appreciation Day & Rocket Roundup Day

Selmaville will be hosting two events in front of the school on Tuesday, May 5th starting at 5 PM.

With May 5th being teacher appreciation day, our staff wants to pay tribute to those parents who have taken on this "teacher" role during this time away from school.

May 5th will also be a time for us to distribute the personal belongings back to our students, in a safe manner, that they left here at the end of the 3rd quarter.

More details on these events will be provided soon.

post_text: Update on the PTO Show Me Dough fundraiser: Orders were due Monday, March 16th. However, with the school closures and precautions taking place, we will not be able to proceed with the original delivery date of 3/30. The new RESCHEDULED DELIVERY DATE is tentatively set for APRIL 7th from 5-6pm. With the new delivery date, we are able to extend our online orders ONLY to 4/1. post_text: Selmaville School will be doing our best to meet the needs of our students during this unprecedented time in our state. One thing we will do is partner with local churches to provide lunches to those who need them. If you have Selmaville students who need lunches delivered to your home please call the school Monday (3/16/2020) to make this request. Also, it is very important that all Selmaville students are at school on Monday the 16th as well, unless they are ill. Review packets will be sent home with each student. We will share more information as it becomes available.
